
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv


mkdir visualization_project
cd visualization_project



python3 -m venv venv



source venv/bin/activate


pip install --upgrade pip
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn streamlit
pip install --upgrade --force-reinstall reportlab
pip install --upgrade scikit-learn




nano app_enhanced.py

- Copy and paste the entire code from the `app_enhanced.py` file
- Press `Ctrl + X`, then `Y`, then `Enter` to save



streamlit run app_enhanced.py


python3 app_enhanced.py


### **Step 9: View Output**

- If Streamlit: Open your browser and go to `http://localhost:8501`
- If Regular Python: Charts will display in a window or save to files


### **Step 10: Deactivate Virtual Environment (when done)**

```shellscript
deactivate
```

---

## **Complete Quick Command (Copy & Paste All at Once)**

```shellscript
mkdir visualization_project && cd visualization_project && \
python3 -m venv venv && \
source venv/bin/activate && \
pip install --upgrade pip && \
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn streamlit
```

Then create your file and run it:

```shellscript
nano app_enhanced.py
# Paste code here, save with Ctrl+X, Y, Enter
streamlit run app_enhanced.py
```
